Description: Fragment of body of thick-walled pottery transport amphora; coarse non-micaceous clay. Cream slip. Incised inscription.
Curator's comments: The clay could be Mareotic, and therefore of Ptolemaic date, while the graffito seems not later than Classical.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 427)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JA.093)
